createCampaign(bytes32,uint256,address,u.details: Creates a new reward campaign. Transfers the specified amount of reward tokens from the caller to the contract.

params._endsAt: The timestamp when the campaign ends.
params._pool: The address of the liquidity pool.
params._rewardAmount: The total amount of reward tokens to be distributed.
params._rewardToken: The address of the ERC20 reward token.
params._startsAt: The timestamp when the campaign starts.

lockAcquired(bytes).details: Helper function when the hook needs to get a lock from the vault. See      https://github.com/pancakeswap/pancake-v4-hooks oh hooks which perform vault.lock()

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

poolManager().notice: The address of the pool manager
